**Definition**
A header in jQuery Mobile is a top-of-page layout widget that provides a consistent title bar and optional navigation buttons for mobile pages.

**Types**

* Standard header
* Header with buttons
* Fixed header
* Themed header

**Working**
The header is created using a `<div>` with `data-role="header"`. jQuery Mobile styles it automatically and places it at the top of the page. You can add titles, back buttons, or navigation controls inside it.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
[ Header ]
[ Title / Buttons ]
-------------------
[ Page Content ]
```

**Advantages**

* Provides consistent top navigation
* Automatically styled for mobile
* Supports buttons and themes
* Can be fixed for persistent navigation

**Disadvantages**

* Too many buttons can clutter small screens
* Fixed headers reduce visible content area

**Examples**

```html
<div data-role="header">
  <h1>My App</h1>
</div>
```

Header with a button:

```html
<div data-role="header">
  <a href="#" data-icon="back">Back</a>
  <h1>Page Title</h1>
</div>
```

**Short code snippets**
Fixed header:

```html
<div data-role="header" data-position="fixed">
```

**Applications**

* Page titles
* Navigation bars
* Back buttons and menus
* Branding sections in mobile apps
